The paper deals with image super-resolution using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and multi-level densely connected networks (DCNs) also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the proposed method to MRI images suggests a possible connection to medical imaging (cs.MM). Finally, the use of deep neural networks for image processing also suggests a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
